articles.content: Suspected cases of gastroenteritis are being investigated after 147 students at North View Primary School (NVPS) developed symptoms last week. In a joint statement on Monday (Jan 19), the Singapore Food Agency (SFA), the Communicable Diseases Agency (CDA) and NVPS said that students across levels were affected. Since the incident, NVPS has also taken precautionary measures including cleaning and sanitising all classrooms and common areas...
